    <h1>Turkish Angora</h1>
    <img class="breed-photo" src="<%= ResolveUrl("~/html1/Pics/breeds/turkish-angora.jpg") %>" alt="Turkish Angora cat" />
    <p>The Turkish Angora is one of the world’s oldest and most elegant cat breeds, celebrated for its silky, flowing coat, graceful movements, and playful yet affectionate nature. Originating in Turkey centuries ago—particularly around the Ankara region, formerly known as Angora—this breed has long been regarded as a national treasure and even appears in Turkish folklore and palaces. The Turkish Angora is known for its striking beauty: it has a long, fine, and silky coat that shimmers as it moves, most famously in pure white, though it also comes in many other colors such as black, blue, cream, red, and even tabby or bi-color patterns. Their eyes are one of their most enchanting features — large, almond-shaped, and often brightly colored in shades of blue, green, amber, or even one of each (a trait called heterochromia). With their slender yet strong build, plumed tail, and regal posture, Turkish Angoras embody grace and sophistication in every movement.

Beyond their stunning looks, Turkish Angoras are known for their lively, intelligent, and affectionate personalities. They are highly social cats that thrive on human companionship, often forming strong attachments to one particular person while still being friendly with everyone in the household. Energetic and agile, they love to climb, jump, and explore high places, often perching on shelves or doorframes to observe their surroundings like little guardians of the home. They are also playful and interactive, enjoying games of chase or fetch, and can remain kitten-like well into adulthood. Despite their active and sometimes mischievous nature, they are gentle and loving, often seeking out cuddles or resting quietly near their favorite human. Turkish Angoras are also known for their intelligence — they can open doors, learn commands, and seem to understand their owners’ moods remarkably well.

Overall, the Turkish Angora is a perfect blend of elegance, intelligence, and affection. With their ethereal beauty, lively spirit, and deep devotion to their human companions, they bring both warmth and sophistication to any home. Whether they’re gracefully strutting across the room or curling up beside you with a soft purr, the Turkish Angora never fails to leave an impression of pure charm and timeless grace.
 </p>
